episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: We meet the five new powerhouse Sharks who have taken over the Tank, where aspiring entrepreneurs pitch their innovative ideas and seek investment from the panel of seasoned business moguls.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: In this episode, Nail polish for men, a video games museum, a self-cleaning dog toilet and a 3D-printed set of designer wheels, Topping it off with a uniquely Australian drink.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: The Shark Tank is open, and pitches include an ice facial tool, science kits for kids and a Thai sauce. Finally, cousins Frank and Frank pull on the heartstrings of the Sharks.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Tonight, an entrepreneur hoping to keep a craft from her homeland alive, taking the backache out of toddler feeding and a trio of children's entertainers pitch to the Sharks in song!

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: We meet entrepreneurs hoping to persuade our Sharks to invest a large cash sum into their business. Also, environmentally friendly nappies, a new version of a Christmas tree and electric scooters!

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tonight, an entrepreneur is offered one million dollars! With innovative products ranging from tattoos to condoms and swimwear to chicken accessories, who will receive massive cash investment?

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Mixed reactions from the Sharks tonight as a string of memorable Entrepreneurs enter the Tank. From a nostalgic camera to a new style of earphone, who will sink and who will swim?

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Each Shark will dive headfirst into new, innovative, and extraordinary products, including a new sunscreen for children and a suit hire rental business.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Australia's sharpest business brains are back with sharper teeth. With the Sharks putting their own money in the stakes are high. Lives will pivot as Entrepreneurs fight for their ideas.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: WA inventors seek $1 million to launch their world's first electric hydrofoil; a construction manager wows with a fashion product; doctors pitch their solution for children with allergies.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: A small business owner with an unexciting product has the Sharks in a frenzy when she reveals sales numbers; Nick Bell locks horns with an entrepreneur seeking a lot of money for little equity.
